To make the button smaller and add rounded corners, you can adjust the CSS. You can add inline styles directly to the button, or, preferably, use a separate CSS class. Here's how you can modify your button with inline styles:

```html
<button class="btn btn-xs" id="btnRed" name="btnRed" style="background-color: red; color: white; padding: 5px 10px; border-radius: 10px;">
    Sickness
</button>
```

Alternatively, you can define a CSS class and apply it to your button:

```html
<style>
    .custom-btn {
        background-color: red;
        color: white;
        padding: 5px 10px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        font-size: 12px; /* Adjust the font size as needed */
    }
</style>

<button class="btn btn-xs custom-btn" id="btnRed" name="btnRed">
    Sickness
</button>
```

This approach keeps your HTML cleaner and separates your styles from your markup.